The police have arraigned an 86-year-old man, Buhari Musa, for allegedly stealing N10,000 worth of maize. Buhari, who resides at the Itanla area of Ado-Ekiti, is facing trial for stealing before an Ado-Ekiti Chief Magistrates’ Court. File photo used to illustrate story. He, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge, Vanguard reports. The prosecutor, Inspector Johnson Okunade, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on June 13 at 7.00 am in the Omisanjana area of Ado-Ekiti. Okunade said that the defendant stole the maize from the complainant, Saliu Mustapha. He said the defendant was caught on the complainant’s farm with the maize. Okunade said the alleged offence contravened Section 390(9) of the Criminal Law of Ekiti State, 2012. The prosecutor urged the court to adjourn the case to enable him to assemble witnesses. Counsel for the defendant, Lai Obisesan, urged the court to grant his client bail, promising that he would not jump bail. The Chief Magistrate, Mr. Adedayo Oyebanji, granted the defendant bail in the sum of N20,000 with one surety in like sum. Adedayo adjourned the case until July 8 for mention.